CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 15, 1941, pg. 1, reads: "Dan Cupid Ready for Action - Dan Cupid is always busy this time of year. Especially on Valentine Day.  We sneaked up on Cupid just as he was reaching for his arrow and snapped his picture.  Cupid in this instance is Master Robert William Goode, son of Mr. and Mrs. Malvin Goode of Anaheim street.  He has been around about nine months. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Baby Robert William Goode dressed as Cupid with bow and arrow, and seated on table
